SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 983
By Southerland
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate Wyatt Epley on
winning the Tennessee AAU wrestling
championship in the 12-and-under, 140-pound
weight class.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that this General Assembly should salute those student athletes
who, through their extraordinary efforts, have distinguished themselves as true champions of
whom we can all be proud; and
WHEREAS, Wyatt Epley, an eleven-year-old student at Newport Grammar School,
recently won the gold medal in the 12-and-under, 140-pound weight class at the Tennessee
AAU wrestling championships; and
WHEREAS, Wyatt Epley dominated his bracket en route to winning the AAU state title at
the Williamson County Ag Expo Park in Franklin; and
WHEREAS, Wyatt Epley pinned his opponent in 1:39 in the quarterfinals; he then
proceeded to earn another pin in the semifinals, taking 1:21 to defeat his opponent and reach
the championship match; and
WHEREAS, in the final match, Wyatt Epley earned a 17-0 technical fall against his
opponent to take home the gold medal as state champion; and
WHEREAS, as he basked in the glow of this special moment, Wyatt Epley modestly
expressed his gratitude for the support of his family during his long and arduous journey to the
state title, including his father, Lucas Epley; his mother, Brittany Epley; his stepmother, Emma
Epley; his stepfather Jessy Burgess; and his grandfather, Chris Epley; and
WHEREAS, Wyatt Epley epitomizes all that is good in today's student athlete, as he has
achieved a high level of success in athletic competition while demonstrating great character
both on and off the wrestling mat; and
SJR0983
015812
- 1 -

WHEREAS, it is fitting for us to salute this elite athlete upon his Tennessee AAU
wrestling championship; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we honor and congratulate Wyatt Epley on winning
the Tennessee AAU wrestling championship in the 12-and-under, 140-pound weight class and
extend to him our best wishes for every future success and happiness.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
